{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"101cc94d-2a28-453a-93a5-2e12e894a09f","content":"The template is **functional but not quite publish-ready**. Here's what I found:\n\n**✅ Present & correct:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`\n- `sourceName` for rename-on-create\n- `classifications`, `tags` (language + type)\n- `symbols` with a valid Framework choice parameter\n\n**⚠️ Missing for NuGet publishing:**\n\n| Field | Why it matters |\n|---|---|\n| `$schema` | Enables editor validation (`https://json.schemastore.org/template`) |\n| `description` | Shown on NuGet.org and in `dotnet new search` — critical for discoverability |\n| `groupIdentity` | Groups multiple related templates (e.g., across languages); recommended best practice |\n| `preferNameDirectory` | Usually `true` for project templates so `dotnet new mywebapi -n Foo` creates a `Foo/` folder |\n\n**💡 Also note:**\n- You'll need a `.nupkg` wrapper (a `.csproj` with `<PackageType>Template</PackageType>`) to actually push to NuGet — the `template.json` alone isn't enough.\n- The directory only contains `.template.config/` — no actual project source files are present yet.\n\n**Verdict:** Add at least `description` and `$schema`, include the actual template source files, and create a packaging project before publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"55cc80ac-4020-4519-b45e-800aba42d631","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review the template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. Let me check what's required for a .NET template package.\n\nKey things to check for a dotnet template:\n1. `$schema` - recommended but not required\n2. `identity` - ✅ present\n3. `name` - ✅ present\n4. `shortName` - ✅ present\n5. `author` - ✅ present\n6. `classifications` - ✅ present\n7. `tags` - ✅ present with language and type\n8. `sourceName` - ✅ present\n\n\n9. `preferNameDirectory` - optional\n10. `groupIdentity` - recommended for NuGet\n11. `precedence` - optional\n12. `description` - missing! This is important for NuGet discoverability\n\nThe template has the core structure down, but it's missing a few key fields that would improve NuGet discoverability—specifically the `description` field and the `$schema` for validation, plus `groupIdentity` which is recommended for better organization on NuGet.","outputTokens":594},"id":"8741d958-1f1e-449a-bdba-ea3cfb9ed120","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:20.691Z","parentId":"e1249d3b-59fe-4ce1-9c8b-99758e4db5f2"}
